<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span id="coordinates"><a href="/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system" title="Geographic coordinate system">Coordinates</a>: <span class="plainlinks nourlexpansion"><a class="external text" href="//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Skellingthorpe&amp;params=53.236431_N_-0.616514_E_region:GB_type:city(3444)"><span class="geo-nondefault"><span class="geo-dms" title="Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location"><span class="latitude">53°14′11″N</span> <span class="longitude">0°36′59″W</span></span></span><span class="geo-multi-punct">﻿ / ﻿</span><span class="geo-default"><span class="geo-dec" title="Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location">53.236431°N 0.616514°W</span><span style="display:none">﻿ / <span class="geo">53.236431; -0.616514</span></span></span></a></span></span></span></p>
<p><b>Skellingthorpe</b> is a village and <a href="/wiki/Civil_parishes_in_England" title="Civil parishes in England">civil parish</a> in the <a href="/wiki/North_Kesteven" title="North Kesteven">North Kesteven</a> district of <a href="/wiki/Lincolnshire" title="Lincolnshire">Lincolnshire</a>, England. It is situated 3 miles (5&#160;km) west from <a href="/wiki/Lincoln,_Lincolnshire" title="Lincoln, Lincolnshire" class="mw-redirect">Lincoln</a> city centre, and just outside the <a href="/wiki/A46_road" title="A46 road">A46</a> Lincoln <a href="/wiki/Ring_road" title="Ring road">ring road</a>.</p>
<p>The village of <a href="/wiki/Doddington,_Lincolnshire" title="Doddington, Lincolnshire">Doddington</a> and <a href="/wiki/Doddington_Hall,_Lincolnshire" title="Doddington Hall, Lincolnshire">Doddington Hall</a> lie 1 mile (1.6&#160;km) to the south-west. <a href="/wiki/Birchwood_(Lincoln)" title="Birchwood (Lincoln)" class="mw-redirect">Birchwood</a> estate, built in the 1970s on the site of <a href="/wiki/RAF_Skellingthorpe" title="RAF Skellingthorpe">RAF Skellingthorpe</a>, is 1 mile to the south-east.</p>
<p></p>
